result.adr_address: 4018, IFC, 1 Harbour View St, Central, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 4018, IFC, 1 Harbour View St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Shake Shack

reviews.text:
Before I went there everyone told
Me to go and eat there, didn’t know if it’s that good.

It is! Great burger, not expensive and delicious!
With a great view of Hong Kong!

Definitely one of the best.

Can be a bit crowded in some hours so prepare to search for a place to sit !

The burgers were great as ever but there were a few things that set this one apart.  1.  The automated hand washing machine.  Awesome to me after walking around outside all day and a huge hit with all the children in the restaurant.  2.  Very short line even on a busy day here.  3.  The atmosphere was awesome.  Big open space, great music, indoor/outdoor spaces.  Overall awesome.  If you want something different try the HK style custard.  Not too far from the usual but good.  Oh, and t-shirts max out at XL.

Food came out piping hot and very fresh. Flavorful patties and soft buns. Fresh toppings - tomatoes and lettuce, but mostly patties in the burger. Clean store and they have indoor / outdoor dining areas. They also serve beers.
Burger and hot dog Could’ve been bigger. Burger definitely better than the hot dog. The drinks were better than the food (root beer float was delicious!)
Very very yummy. Affordable. About $50-60 per burger and an addition $30 for fries. Recommended.

result.formatted_address: International Finance Center, 8 Finance St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: International Finance Center

reviews.text: Good for public transportation transit areas.  There are mall with famous brands for tourists & local middle classes.  Well-known supermarket & plenty of restaurants as well as fast-food shops.  Also have theatres provide entertainment for family leisure time.
High end mall, great ambiance and has direct airport bag and boarding pass check inn! Now you can enjoy the city instead of rushing to the airport and roaming around with your luggage.
My only real experience is walking through IFC on my way to and from the ferry. Do appreciate the ac and conveniently located city super.

It’s a well located mall with a good choice of stores and restaurants. The exchange square is a central bus station which is close by. The airport express in town check in is located on the ground level and the train station is located below. The Macau ferry stop is walking distance from here through the bridges as well as the central ferry pier.

Awesome mall. They have everything from ships, movie theaters, to upscale restaurants and more low-key joints. They also have the airport express there which is one of the quickest ways to get to the airport. Definitely great to catch up with friends or bring your guests for a fun afternoon!

reviews.text: 好吃的漢堡🍔呦
好吃😋

Burger有試過Chick’n Shack($56)和Shroom Burger($66)。
前者的話是不會有下一次，雞肉非常乾；後者非常美味，很juice，回頭之選。

Cheese Fries($36)就普通了點，太軟，不香口。

不得不說！Classic Hand-Spun Shakes的coffee味真的非常不錯，試過一次以後經常都掛念著！
